#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.30"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.30:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.30:0.2"
msgid "3. Uruvelavagga"
msgstr "3. At Uruvelā"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.30:0.3"
msgid "30. Paribbājakasutta"
msgstr "30. Wanderers"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an4.30:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak "
"Mountain."

#. VAR: sippinikātīre → sappiniyātīre (bj, pts1) | sippiniyā tīre (s1-3, km) | sippiniyā nadiyā tīre (mr)
msgctxt "an4.30:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā abhiññātā abhiññātā paribbājakā "
"sippinikātīre paribbājakārāme paṭivasanti, seyyathidaṃ annabhāro varadharo "
"sakuludāyī ca paribbājako aññe ca abhiññātā abhiññātā paribbājakā."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time several very well-known wanderers were residing in the "
"monastery of the wanderers on the bank of the Sappinī river. They included "
"Annabhāra, Varadhara, Sakuludāyī, and other very well-known wanderers."

msgctxt "an4.30:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena sippinikātīraṃ "
"paribbājakārāmo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi. Nisajja "
"kho bhagavā te paribbājake etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then in the late afternoon, the Buddha came out of retreat and went to the "
"wanderer’s monastery on the banks of the Sappinī river, He sat down on the "
"seat spread out, and said to the wanderers:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.30"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.30:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Cattārimāni, paribbājakā, dhammapadāni aggaññāni rattaññāni vaṃsaññāni "
"porāṇāni asaṅkiṇṇāni asaṅkiṇṇapubbāni, na saṅkīyanti na saṅkīyissanti, "
"appaṭikuṭṭhāni samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhi."
msgstr ""
"“Wanderers, these four basic principles are original, long-standing, "
"traditional, and ancient. They are uncorrupted, as they have been since the "
"beginning. They’re not being corrupted now nor will they be. Sensible "
"ascetics and brahmins don’t look down on them."

msgctxt "an4.30:2.2"
msgid "Katamāni cattāri?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "an4.30:2.3"
msgid ""
"Anabhijjhā, paribbājakā, dhammapadaṃ aggaññaṃ rattaññaṃ vaṃsaññaṃ porāṇaṃ "
"asaṅkiṇṇaṃ asaṅkiṇṇapubbaṃ, na saṅkīyati na saṅkīyissati, appaṭikuṭṭhaṃ "
"samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhi."
msgstr "Contentment …"

msgctxt "an4.30:2.4"
msgid ""
"Abyāpādo, paribbājakā, dhammapadaṃ … pe … sammāsati, paribbājakā, "
"dhammapadaṃ … pe … sammāsamādhi, paribbājakā, dhammapadaṃ aggaññaṃ rattaññaṃ "
"vaṃsaññaṃ porāṇaṃ asaṅkiṇṇaṃ asaṅkiṇṇapubbaṃ, na saṅkīyati na saṅkīyissati, "
"appaṭikuṭṭhaṃ samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhi."
msgstr "Good will … Right mindfulness … Right immersion …"

msgctxt "an4.30:2.5"
msgid ""
"Imāni kho, paribbājakā, cattāri dhammapadāni aggaññāni rattaññāni vaṃsaññāni "
"porāṇāni asaṅkiṇṇāni asaṅkiṇṇapubbāni, na saṅkīyanti na saṅkīyissanti, "
"appaṭikuṭṭhāni samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhi."
msgstr ""
"These four basic principles are original, long-standing, traditional, and "
"ancient. They are uncorrupted, as they have been since the beginning. They’"
"re not being corrupted now nor will they be. Sensible ascetics and brahmins "
"don’t look down on them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.30:3.1"
msgid "Yo kho, paribbājakā, evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "Wanderers, if someone should say:"

msgctxt "an4.30:3.2"
msgid ""
"‘ahametaṃ anabhijjhaṃ dhammapadaṃ paccakkhāya abhijjhāluṃ kāmesu "
"tibbasārāgaṃ samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā paññāpessāmī’ti, tamahaṃ tattha evaṃ "
"vadeyyaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"‘I’ll reject this basic principle of contentment, and describe a true "
"ascetic or brahmin who covets sensual pleasures with acute lust.’ Then I’d "
"say to them:"

msgctxt "an4.30:3.3"
msgid "‘etu vadatu byāharatu passāmissānubhāvan’ti."
msgstr "‘Let them come, speak, and discuss. We’ll see how powerful they are.’"

msgctxt "an4.30:3.4"
msgid ""
"So vata, paribbājakā, anabhijjhaṃ dhammapadaṃ paccakkhāya abhijjhāluṃ kāmesu "
"tibbasārāgaṃ samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā paññāpessatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"It’s simply impossible to reject this basic principle of contentment, and "
"point out a true ascetic or brahmin who covets sensual pleasures with acute "
"lust."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an4.30:4.1"
msgid "Yo kho, paribbājakā, evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "If someone should say:"

msgctxt "an4.30:4.2"
msgid ""
"‘ahametaṃ abyāpādaṃ dhammapadaṃ paccakkhāya byāpannacittaṃ "
"paduṭṭhamanasaṅkappaṃ samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā paññāpessāmī’ti, tamahaṃ "
"tattha evaṃ vadeyyaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"‘I’ll reject this basic principle of good will, and describe a true ascetic "
"or brahmin who has ill will and hateful intent.’ Then I’d say to them:"

msgctxt "an4.30:4.3"
msgid "‘etu vadatu byāharatu passāmissānubhāvan’ti."
msgstr "‘Let them come, speak, and discuss. We’ll see how powerful they are.’"

msgctxt "an4.30:4.4"
msgid ""
"So vata, paribbājakā, abyāpādaṃ dhammapadaṃ paccakkhāya byāpannacittaṃ "
"paduṭṭhamanasaṅkappaṃ samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā paññāpessatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ "
"vijjati."
msgstr ""
"It’s simply impossible to reject this basic principle of good will, and "
"point out a true ascetic or brahmin who has ill will and hateful intent."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an4.30:5.1"
msgid "Yo kho, paribbājakā, evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "If someone should say:"

msgctxt "an4.30:5.2"
msgid ""
"‘ahametaṃ sammāsatiṃ dhammapadaṃ paccakkhāya muṭṭhassatiṃ asampajānaṃ "
"samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā paññāpessāmī’ti, tamahaṃ tattha evaṃ vadeyyaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"‘I’ll reject this basic principle of right mindfulness, and describe a true "
"ascetic or brahmin who is unmindful, with no situational awareness.’ Then I’"
"d say to them:"

msgctxt "an4.30:5.3"
msgid "‘etu vadatu byāharatu passāmissānubhāvan’ti."
msgstr "‘Let them come, speak, and discuss. We’ll see how powerful they are.’"

msgctxt "an4.30:5.4"
msgid ""
"So vata, paribbājakā, sammāsatiṃ dhammapadaṃ paccakkhāya muṭṭhassatiṃ "
"asampajānaṃ samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā paññāpessatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"It’s simply impossible to reject this basic principle of right mindfulness, "
"and point out a true ascetic or brahmin who is unmindful, with no "
"situational awareness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.31"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an4.30:6.1"
msgid "Yo kho, paribbājakā, evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "If someone should say:"

msgctxt "an4.30:6.2"
msgid ""
"‘ahametaṃ sammāsamādhiṃ dhammapadaṃ paccakkhāya asamāhitaṃ vibbhantacittaṃ "
"samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā paññāpessāmī’ti, tamahaṃ tattha evaṃ vadeyyaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"‘I’ll reject this basic principle of right immersion, and describe a true "
"ascetic or brahmin who is scattered, with straying mind.’ Then I’d say to "
"them:"

msgctxt "an4.30:6.3"
msgid "‘etu vadatu byāharatu passāmissānubhāvan’ti."
msgstr "‘Let them come, speak, and discuss. We’ll see how powerful they are.’"

msgctxt "an4.30:6.4"
msgid ""
"So vata, paribbājakā, sammāsamādhiṃ dhammapadaṃ paccakkhāya asamāhitaṃ "
"vibbhantacittaṃ samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā paññāpessatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"It’s simply impossible to reject this basic principle of right immersion, "
"and point out a true ascetic or brahmin who is scattered, with straying mind."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an4.30:7.1"
msgid ""
"Yo kho, paribbājakā, imāni cattāri dhammapadāni garahitabbaṃ paṭikkositabbaṃ "
"maññeyya, tassa diṭṭheva dhamme cattāro sahadhammikā vādānupātā gārayhā "
"ṭhānā āgacchanti."
msgstr ""
"If anyone imagines they can criticize and reject these four basic "
"principles, they deserve rebuke and criticism on four legitimate grounds in "
"the present life."

msgctxt "an4.30:7.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "an4.30:7.3"
msgid ""
"Anabhijjhañce bhavaṃ dhammapadaṃ garahati paṭikkosati, ye ca hi abhijjhālū "
"kāmesu tibbasārāgā samaṇabrāhmaṇā te bhoto pujjā te bhoto pāsaṃsā."
msgstr ""
"If you reject the basic principle of contentment, then you must honor and "
"praise those ascetics and brahmins who covet sensual pleasures with acute "
"lust."

msgctxt "an4.30:7.4"
msgid ""
"Abyāpādañce bhavaṃ dhammapadaṃ garahati paṭikkosati, ye ca hi byāpannacittā "
"paduṭṭhamanasaṅkappā samaṇabrāhmaṇā te bhoto pujjā te bhoto pāsaṃsā."
msgstr ""
"If you reject the basic principle of good will, you must honor and praise "
"those ascetics and brahmins who have ill will and hateful intent."

msgctxt "an4.30:7.5"
msgid ""
"Sammāsatiñce bhavaṃ dhammapadaṃ garahati paṭikkosati, ye ca hi muṭṭhassatī "
"asampajānā samaṇabrāhmaṇā te bhoto pujjā te bhoto pāsaṃsā."
msgstr ""
"If you reject the basic principle of right mindfulness, then you must honor "
"and praise those ascetics and brahmins who are unmindful, with no "
"situational awareness."

msgctxt "an4.30:7.6"
msgid ""
"Sammāsamādhiñce bhavaṃ dhammapadaṃ garahati paṭikkosati, ye ca hi asamāhitā "
"vibbhantacittā samaṇabrāhmaṇā te bhoto pujjā te bhoto pāsaṃsā."
msgstr ""
"If you reject the basic principle of right immersion, you must honor and "
"praise those ascetics and brahmins who are scattered, with straying minds."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an4.30:8.1"
msgid ""
"Yo kho, paribbājakā, imāni cattāri dhammapadāni garahitabbaṃ paṭikkositabbaṃ "
"maññeyya, tassa diṭṭheva dhamme ime cattāro sahadhammikā vādānupātā gārayhā "
"ṭhānā āgacchanti."
msgstr ""
"If anyone imagines they can criticize and reject these four basic "
"principles, they deserve rebuke and criticism on four legitimate grounds in "
"the present life."

#. VAR: vassabhaññā → vassaṃ bhaññā (pts1) | vassabhiññā (mr)
msgctxt "an4.30:8.2"
msgid ""
"Yepi te paribbājakā ahesuṃ ukkalā vassabhaññā ahetukavādā akiriyavādā "
"natthikavādā, tepi imāni cattāri dhammapadāni na garahitabbaṃ na "
"paṭikkositabbaṃ amaññiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Even those wanderers of the past, Vassa and Bhañña of Ukkalā, who taught the "
"doctrines of no-cause, inaction, and nihilism, didn’t imagine that these "
"four basic principles should be criticized or rejected."

msgctxt "an4.30:8.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

#. VAR: Nindābyārosanaupārambhabhayāti → nindābyārosā upārambhabhayati (bj) | … upavādabhayāti (mr)
msgctxt "an4.30:8.4"
msgid "Nindābyārosanaupārambhabhayāti."
msgstr "For fear of being blamed, criticized, and faulted."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an4.30:9.1"
msgid "Abyāpanno sadā sato,"
msgstr "One who has good will, ever mindful,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.30:9.2"
msgid "ajjhattaṃ susamāhito;"
msgstr "serene within,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.30:9.3"
msgid "Abhijjhāvinaye sikkhaṃ,"
msgstr "training to remove desire,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.30:9.4"
msgid "appamattoti vuccatī”ti."
msgstr "is called ‘a diligent one’.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.30:9.5"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.30:9.6"
msgid "Uruvelavaggo tatiyo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
#. VAR: kāḷako → kāliko (bj) | kāḷiko (pts1) | koḷiko (mr)
msgctxt "an4.30:10.1"
msgid "Dve uruvelā loko kāḷako,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.30:10.2"
msgid "Brahmacariyena pañcamaṃ;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.30:10.3"
msgid "Kuhaṃ santuṭṭhi vaṃso ca,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.30:10.4"
msgid "Dhammapadaṃ paribbājakena cāti."
msgstr ""
